    "patch_code": "public int read(byte b[], int off, int len) throws IOException {\n    \tif (b == null) {\n\t    throw new NullPointerException();\n\t} else if ((off < 0) || (off > b.length) || (len < 0) ||\n\t       ((off + len) > b.length)){\n\t    throw new IndexOutOfBoundsException();\n\t}\n\n\t// If len is smaller than 3, then copy as much data into\n\t// the buffer and try to decode them immediately to bypass\n\t// the problems caused by returning less than len during\n\t// reading.\n\tint n = 0;\n\tif (len >= 3){\n\t\tn = in.read(b, off, len - 5);\n\t\tbase64.update(b, off, off + 2);\n\t\t\n\t\t// If no enough data is read, read more data\n\t\t// until enough data is obtained.\n\t\twhile(n < len){\n\t\t\tn += in.read(b, off + n, len - n);\n\t\t}\n\t}else{\n\t\tn = in.read(b, off, len);\n\t}\n\treturn n;\n    }",
